recipe.label: Portuguese Seafood Stew that Reminds Us of Portugal
ingredientLines: 1/2 pound medium-large shrimp, peeled and deveined, shells reserved
2 teaspoons olive oil, plus more to serve
1 large, sweet onion, halved pole to pole and sliced
1 large bulb fennel, sliced thin, fronds reserved
4 Yukon gold potatoes, cut into approximately 1-inch pieces
4 plum tomatoes, peeled, seeded, and chopped (use canned in the winter and spring)
2 cups white wine (that you like to drink)
2 pounds fresh white fish filets (I usually use two types of fish—whatever is freshest)
Juice and zest of 1/2 lemon, preferably Meyer
Red pepper flakes or Aleppo pepper as desired (plus more if desired)
1 teaspoon fennel seed, crushed with mortar and pestle or ground in spice grinder (or more to taste)

recipe.label: Very "Saucy" Seafood Rice – Arroz de Marisco Malandro (Portugal)
ingredientLines: 2 1/2 cups medium grain rice, not washed
3 cups shrimp broth (from cooking the shrimp)
2 cups clam/mussels broth (from cooking the clams and mussels)
1 1/2 pounds whole fresh shrimp (or lobster and crab)
1 pound very fresh mussels in their shells
1 pound very fresh clams in their shells
2 medium carrots, peeled and cut in medium cubes
2 cups fresh tomatoes, skin and seeds removed and cut in pieces or use canned tomatoes in pieces
1 piece of green pepper the size of a thumb, no seeds, cut in strips (optional)
2 garlic cloves finely chopped, without the inner green part
2 whole garlic cloves crushed, not peeled
1 or 2 dry red chillies (depends how hot you like your food)
